@reduz If only one model is needed in a scene with swapping several models, it is obviously redundant to always have two Skeletons and need a SkeletonRetarget node when using retargeted animations.

If you don't include that mode in your animation, we can store all BoneRests in the animation data, and for example, for rotation with GlobalAnimation, you will need to multiply the quaternion 6 times during playback.

However, with the method I implemented, we can split the process into two parts: extract and apply. When playback animation, all that is required is to multiply the quaternion 3 times in the apply process. However, since we cannot know how the extraction was done just from the value of the quaternion, we need to store the mode in the Animation. Retargeting will break if the extraction and application processes are in different modes.

